{"name":"A World","permission":{"default":0,"6tM65gLPv3vengSW":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1>Environment</h1>\n<p>What&rsquo;s the environment like in the area where the heroes will explore? Are there barren deserts? High mountains? Thick swamps? Frigid glaciers? Airless chasms? Is it a luxurious deep space colony, or a worn-out orbital habitat?</p>\n<h1>Population</h1>\n<p>How densely populated is this place? If one culture dominates the area, what are those people like?</p>\n<h1>Society</h1>\n<p>Is this a rigid police state, or does violence and anarchy reign? Are the people here prosperous, or starving? Do they have state-of-the-art galactic technology, or are they still learning the secrets of physics and chemistry?</p>\n<h1>Resources</h1>\n<p>What&rsquo;s valuable here? Why would anyone come here?</p>\n<h1>Hazards</h1>\n<p>What&rsquo;s dangerous here? What should the heroes worry about?</p>\n<h1>Enemy</h1>\n<p>What resources does the Enemy have here?</p>\n<h1>Resistance</h1>\n<p>Is there a Resistance presence, and if so, what does it look like?</p>","_id":"6CSZ8zh4VGmZIM38"}
{"name":"The Ship","permission":{"default":0,"6tM65gLPv3vengSW":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p><strong>In this universe, ships achieve faster-than-light (FTL) travel through:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Warp drives (ships move rapidly through normal space)</li>\n<li>Jump drives (ships teleport from point to point)</li>\n<li>Hyperspace (ships move through extradimensional space)</li>\n<li>Wormholes (ships travel through naturally occurring cosmic shortcuts)</li>\n<li>Stargates (ships use artificial gateways)</li>\n<li>No FTL (which may mean that the story takes place entirely on one world, or within one star system, or purely through interstellar communication)</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>What&rsquo;s the shortest travel time between two worlds in your game? What&rsquo;s the longest travel time?</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Instantaneous</li>\n<li>Minutes</li>\n<li>Hours</li>\n<li>Days</li>\n<li>Weeks</li>\n<li>Months</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>How big is your ship?</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Small. We each have our own individual single-person spacecraft.</li>\n<li>Medium. Just big enough for the heroes to live in comfortably, with space available for cargo.</li>\n<li>Large. Apart from the heroes, the ship has a dozen or so crew, and might carry a shuttlecraft.</li>\n<li>Huge. Big enough to carry a crew of hundreds and an assortment of smaller craft.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>Choose two advantages for your ship. These are exceptional qualities or equipment your ship possesses.</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Speed and maneuverability</li>\n<li>Stealth</li>\n<li>Firepower</li>\n<li>Concealed storage</li>\n<li>Reputation</li>\n<li>Powerful scanners</li>\n<li>Communication interception and scrambling</li>\n<li>Medical treatment and diagnosis</li>\n<li>Science and engineering</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>Finally, the players should name their ship.</strong></p>","_id":"CpxgehhHxMNjKzmb"}
